PulseDivider.ar(trig, div, startCount)\

\f1\b0 \
Outputs one impulse each time it receives a certain number of triggers at its input.\

\f0\b trig
\f1\b0  - trigger. Trigger can be any signal. A trigger happens when the signal changes from\
non-positive to positive.\

\f0\b div
\f1\b0  - number of pulses to divide by.\

\f0\b startCount
\f1\b0  - starting value for the trigger count. This lets you start somewhere in the middle of a count,\
or if startCount is negative it adds that many counts to the first time the output is triggers.\
